====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[reserve]] (something) for future use.
#: ''I want to '''book''' a hotel room for tomorrow night''
#: ''I can '''book''' tickets for the concert next week.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[write down]], to [[register]] or [[record]] in a book or as in a book.
#: ''They '''booked''' that message from the hill''
# {{context|law enforcement|transitive|lang=en}} To [[record]] the name and other details of a suspected offender and the offence for later judicial action.
#: ''The police '''booked''' him for driving too fast.''
# {{context|sports|lang=en}} To issue with a [[caution]], usually a [[yellow card]], or a [[red card]] if a yellow card has already been issued.
# {{context|intransitive|slang|lang=en}} To travel very fast.
#: ''He was really '''booking''', until he passed the speed trap.''
# To record [[bet|bets]] as [[bookmaker]].
# {{context|transitive|law student slang|lang=en}} To receive the highest [[grade]] in a class.
#: ''The top three students had a bet on which one was going to '''book''' their intellectual property class.''
# {{context|intransitive|slang|lang=en}} To leave.
#: ''He was here earlier, but he '''booked'''.''

