===Etymology 3===
From {{etyl|hi|en}} {{term|‡§™‡§æ‡§à||quarter|tr=pƒÅƒ´|lang=hi}}, from {{etyl|sa|en}} {{term|‡§™‡§æ‡§¶‡§ø‡§ï‡§æ|tr=pƒÅdikƒÅ|lang=sa}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|pie|pies}}

# {{context|historical|lang=en}} The smallest unit of currency in South Asia, equivalent to 1/192 of a [[rupee]] or 1/12 of an [[anna]].
#* '''1888''', Rudyard Kipling, ‚ÄòThe Strange Ride of Morrowbie Jukes‚Äô, ''The Phantom ‚ÄôRickshaw and Other Tales'', Folio Society 2005, page 117:
#*: I gave him all the money in my possession, Rs.9.8.5. ‚Äì nine rupees, eight annas, and five '''pie''' ‚Äì for I always keep small change as ''bakshish'' when I am in camp.

