==English==

===Etymology 1===
[[Image:Runic letter ansuz.png|left|30px|Runic letter {{term||·ö´|tr=a|ansuz|lang=mul}}, source for Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letters replaced by ''A'']]
From {{etyl|enm|en}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|A|lang=enm}} and split of {{etyl|enm|en}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|√Ü|lang=enm}}.
:* [[Image:Rune-Ac.png|10px|Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term||·ö™|tr=a|ƒÅc|lang=mul}}]] {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|A|lang=enm}} from 7th century replacement by Latin upper case letter {{term|A|lang=la}} of the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term|sc=Runr|·ö™||tr=a|ƒÅc|lang=mul}}, derived from Runic letter {{term|sc=Runr|·ö´||tr=a|Ansuz|lang=mul}}.
:* [[Image:Rune-√Üsc.png|10px|Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term||·ö´|tr=√¶|√¶sc|lang=mul}}]] {{etyl|ang|en}} upper case letter {{term|√Ü|lang=enm}} from 7th century replacement by Latin upper case ligature {{term|√Ü|lang=la}} of the Anglo-Saxon Futhorc letter {{term|sc=Runr|·ö´||tr=√¶|√¶sc|lang=mul}}, also derived from Runic letter {{term|sc=Runr|·ö´||tr=a|Ansuz|lang=mul}}.

