===Etymology 1===
[[Image:The Raven.jpg|thumb|right|A raven (bird).]]
{{wikipedia}}
{{wikispecies|Corvus corax}}
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hr√¶fn}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hrabnaz}} (compare {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|raaf}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|Rabe}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{m|da|ravn}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*·∏±orh‚ÇÇ-}} (compare {{etyl|mga|-}} {{m|mga|cr√∫}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|corvus}}, {{etyl|lt|-}} {{m|lt|≈°√°rka||magpie}}, {{etyl|sh|-}} {{m|sh|svr»Åka}} ‚Äòid.‚Äô, {{etyl|grc|-}} {{m|grc|Œ∫œåœÅŒ±Œæ}}), from {{m|ine-pro|*·∏±er}}, {{m|ine-pro|*·∏±or}} (compare {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|crepare}} ‚Äòto creak, crack‚Äô, {{etyl|sa|-}} {{m|sa||k·πõÃÅpatƒì||he laments, implores}}).

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A common name for several, generally large and lustrous black species of [[bird]]s in the genus ''[[Corvus]]'', especially the [[common raven]], ''[[Corvus corax]]''.

